1. Touchdown pass hit the ground - correct call
2. Levelled the punter - correct call
3. Targeting head to head on QB - correct call
4. Fumble overturned to incomplete pass: The rule states the receiver must make a football move which is a 2 step UPFIELD move. According to the rule the call was correct. Don't get mad at the refs for this one. If you don't like the ruling change the rules.

snippet.textDisplay:
The B1G and PAC need to boycott the playoffs until ESPN, SEC, ACC, and the AP are brought to heel. Go back to sending their two best teams to the Rose Bowl regardless of rankings. It can't get much clearer that the fix is in when an SEC officiating crew comes strolling out to judge a semifinals game and then every single controversial call goes in ONE direction.
With each passing year it becomes clearer that the playoffs were a rig to bring the most pleasing and lucrative finals to ESPN's top clients.
